.TH man 1 "22 Nov 2018" "1.0" "spc man page"
.SH NAME
spc \- syncs your data to secure encrypted presonal cloud
.SH SYNOPSIS
spc [OPTION]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
spc helps you to store your encrypted files on your personal server, and synchronise them. You have the freedom of choosing the encryption scheme and key.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B \- config_edit
configure your username and password for easier access

.TP
.B \- set_url [URL]
set the url for your server

.TP
.B \- observe [HOME_DIR]
set the directory to be monitored

.TP
.B \- sync
synchronise local and cloud copy. They are identical after this command

.TP
.B \- print_key
prints the encryption schema and keys

.TP
.B \- version
prints the current version

.TP
.B \- set_key
sets an encryption schema and key before, if there isn't one

.TP
.B \- dump [FILE]
sets the encryption key to the key in the file

.TP
.B \- status
prints the current status of the files

.TP
.B \- en_de_list 
prints all the available encryption schemes

.TP
.B \- en_de_update [FILE]
update the encryption scheme

.TP
.B \- help
list of all commands supported

.TP
.B \- server
prints public information of the server

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH DEVELOPER_TEAM
importteamName
